.TH WT 1 "March 2026" "wt" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
wt \- convenient Git worktree manager

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B wt
.I command
[args]

.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B init
Print shell wrapper (eval "$(wt init)").

.TP
.B add <name>
Create new branch + worktree.

.TP
.B co <name>
Switch to worktree.

.TP
.B rm [-f] [<name>]
Remove worktree.

.TP
.B ignore
Auto-add .worktree/ to .gitignore and stage it.

.TP
.B prune | ls | mv
Standard worktree commands.

.SH FILES
.I <repo>/.worktree/<name>
(and .gitignore now handled automatically)

.SH SEE ALSO
git-worktree(1)
